    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As a manager of a retail business in New York City and a successful eBay seller, I have experienced fraud by buyers in both industries (''A New Caveat for eBay Users: Seller Beware,'' Aug. 3). Maybe I have been smart or lucky, but either way, my experiences online have been primarily successful. The lesson new sellers learn is that this can happen in any business, online or brick and mortar.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As a manager of a retail business in New York City and a successful eBay seller, I have experienced fraud by buyers in both industries (''A New Caveat for eBay Users: Seller Beware,'' Aug. 3). Maybe I have been smart or lucky, but either way, my experiences online have been primarily successful. The lesson new sellers learn is that this can happen in any business, online or brick and mortar.</p>
        <p>When you start to get into transactions of higher dollar values, it is a good idea to use one of the escrow-insurance services like i-Escrow. In general, the mention of such services will scare off fraudulent buyers, just as video cameras in a store might deter fraudulent buyers there.</p>
        <p>BRAD MILES  New York</p>
      </block>
